                            <comment id="60200" author="kdonald" created="Tue, 2 Nov 2010 13:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Value(&quot;request.foo&quot;) might even be better. Assigning to 3.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67181" author="kdonald" created="Wed, 8 Jun 2011 07:53:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m ok with not adding support for this in @Value, so long as it&apos;s documented what is accessible via @Value from a Controller.  Currently it&apos;s not well defined in the docs as to what&apos;s supported, and that&apos;s probably why I opened this.  I&apos;m pretty sure @Value(&quot;request.getAttribute(&apos;foo&apos;) acutally works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
